els as well. The simulations indicate that nonlinear estimation can be\neffective when the Strehl ratio of the input beam is greater than 0.3, and the\nimprovement relative to linear estimation tends to increase at larger Strehl\nratios. At Strehl ratios less than about 0.5, the performances of both the\nnonlinear and linear estimators are relatively insensitive to noise, since they\nare dominated by nonlinearity error.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 Apr 2018 15:06:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-09"}
